review_blob: Keg from north hop beer fest. Pours a clear Amber gold with a lively white head that slowly fades. Nice lacing. Aromas of apricots, prunes and a citrus blast to finish. Flavour is apricot, a fair musky orange. An almost metallic finish.

Can from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a slightly hazed yellow orange with a white frothy head that lasts. Aromas of punchy orange, hay and slight peppery notes. Flavour is juicy orange with grapefruit and a something else I cant put my finger on. Very drinkable!

Bottle from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a deep Amber with a small white head that fades. Aromas of orange zest, lemon and a mild spice hit. Flavour is orange with a citrus kick and a little wood. Nice.

Bottle from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a murky brown with a thick caramel head that lasts. Aromas of fudge, grass and bread. Flavour is caramel, slightly burnt toast and an earthy pine finish. Extremely drinkable.
Bottle shared with the bro. Pours a black with a small toffee head that fades. Aromas of chocolate, milky coffee and mild wood smoke. Flavour is coffee, caramel and chocolate. Lovely.

Bottle shared with the bro! Pours a hazed orange with little head. Aromas of grapefruit and lemon and pine and an open bag of fresh New Zealand hops. Flavour is grapefruit, pineapple with a big pine finish.

Bottle shared with the bro. Pours a black with a thick fudge head that fades slowly. Aroma is sweet raspberry with chocolate milkshake. Flavour is zingy raspberries, chocolate and caramel with a mild salty hit. Lovely!
beer_name: Fallen / BrewDog Big Raspberry Dog Chew

review_blob: Bottle shared with the bro, pours a clear orange with a frothy head. Aroma of squashed prunes, grapefruit, hay, peaches and lemongrass. Flavour is sweet peach with a citrus hit and a big hop chew. Lovely.
Bottle saved with the brother. Pours a clear yellow/orange with a small white head that fades, aroma is orange marmalade, cut grass and caramel. Flavour is big orange pith with a chalky aftertaste.

Bottle from stewart brewery, pours a clear golden with a white frothy head that fades slowly. Aromas of orange zest, tea, with slight woody hints. Flavour is grapefruit and pine with mild earthy notes.
Bottle shared with Jamestulloch. Pours a clear orange with small head. Aromas of orange peel, grass and vine tomatoes. Flavour is orange pith with light citrus and fresh hops.

Bottle shared with the bro. Cheers Jamestulloch! Pours a black with little head. Aromas of chocolate, black pepper and big chocolate. Flavour is sweet chocolate, coffee and then a black pepper spice creeps up and nips the tongue. Mild spicy linger. Surprisingly rather enjoyable.

Bottle shared with Jamestulloch. Cheers bro. Pours a hazy gold with a frothy white head that stays. Aromas of peppery pear, mild lemongrass, stingy nettles and hay. Flavour is musky apricot, caramel and citrus hints. Chalky citrus linger.

Bottle shared with the bro. Cheers Jamestulloch. Pours black with a fudge coloured head that fades slowly. Aromas of coffee, dark chocolate with ripe plums. Flavour is again chocolate with a caramel coffee. Slightly bitter with a enjoyable burnt aftertaste. Lovely.
beer_name: Twisted Barrel The Call of Korriban

review_blob: Bottle shared with the bro. Cheers James! Pours a hazed orange with a small white frothy head. Aromas of juicy melon, tropical fruits, and citrus. Flavour is tropical fruit, citrus, slight pepper hits with a biscuity pine linger.

Bottle shared with the bro. Cheers James! Pours a slightly flaked, yellow/ orange with a nice white head that slowly fades. Aromas of musky peach, grass and white pepper. Flavour is a bitter lemon, with a musky tea with again white pepper notes.

Bottle from buchanans bistro. Labelled as BoHo lager. Pours a hazed yellow with a frothy head that fades down. Nice lacing. Aroma is bitter lemon, hay and a nice yeasty whiff. Flavour is similar with a chalky aftertaste.
beer_name: Quiet Brew No. 4 Pilsner Style Lager

review_blob: Bottle from quiet brewery. Unfortunately this beer was infected. Rubber nose and overly sour to be enjoyed. Tried no1 & no2 beers and they are great. Dont know what happened with this...
beer_name: Quiet Brew No. 5 Wild Wheat Beer

review_blob: Bottle from buchanans bistro. (Quiet brewery) pours a slightly hazed orange/gold with a generous white head that fades quickly. Aromas of ripe pear, sweet dates, earthy grain, citrus fruits and a hint of lemongrass. Flavour is slightly bitter with again pear and citrus. Fantastic beer that is very moreish!
Bottle from Lidls. Pours a ruby red with a small off white head that fades slowly. Aromas of grapefruit, lemon grass and earthy moss. Flavour is grapefruit with a biscuit finish. Brilliant for 1.25!
beer_name: Lidl Hatherwood The Amber Adder Amber Ale No.3

review_blob: Bottle from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a oily black with a fudge head that fades. Aromas of coffee, vanilla, raisins and chocolate. Flavour is chocolate and espresso. Mild hints of vanilla. Very drinkable.
Bottle from flavourly.com pours a clear gold with little head. Aromas of malty biscuit, hay and slight zesty fruit. Flavour is similar with an earthy pine finish.

Bottle from flavourly.com. Pours a clear gold with a small white head that fades. Floral aroma with citrus and malty notes with a hint of caramel, flavour is weaker than expected. Mild malty was and a floral hint. Not bad
Can from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a black with little head that fades. Aromas of treacle, chocolate, mild Citrus and berries. Flavour is similar with a lovely berry/woody linger.

Bottle from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a slightly cloudy gold/brown with small head that stays. Aroma of summer fruits, elderflower and hay. Flavour is a summer fruit hop bomb with a mild pine. Lovely berry fruit linger.

Can from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a clear gold with a thin white head that fades. Nice lacing. Aroma of hay, lemongrass and citrus fruits. Flavour of lemon grass, citrus fruits and mild wood pine. Chalky aftertaste.
Can from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a black with little head that fades. Aromas of caramel, treacle, Creme brle and a hint of dark fruits. Flavour is similar with a sweet finish.

Can from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a dark black with little head that fades quickly. Aromas of coffee, treacle, chocolate and bonfire smoke. Taste is similar with a hint of fruit cake. Nice coffee linger.
beer_name: Northern Monk Northern Star Mocha Porter

review_blob: Bottle from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a clear yellow/orange with an off white head that fades slowly. Aromas of honeydew melon, citrus fruits and coriander leaf. Flavour is a nice hop bomb with similar flavours to the aroma. Pine linger.

boyyle was given as a gift. Pours a reddish black with a small light brown head that fades. Aroma of milk chocolate, coffee and toffee. Flavour is similar however at the same time pretty bland with a watery mouthfeel.

Can from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a light yellow with a large white head that fades slowly. Aromas of crisp zesty Apples and yeast. Flavour is similar but with a sweet cider like finish. Hides the % well.
Can from deeside drinks, pours a hazed brown with a light froth head that fades. Aromas of pine wood, pineapple and grapefruit. Flavour is basically exactly the same with a nice pine finish.

Bottle from formartines. Pours a dark brown with a nice white head that lasts. Aromas of kiwi fruit, pineapple and earthy pine. Flavour is dark chocolate with a light hint of the tropical fruits. Mild pine linger.
Bottle from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a clear red with a light pink head that fades quickly. Aroma of tart raspberry. Flavour is sour raspberrys, quite vinegary finish.

Bottle from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a clear brown with little head. Not much aroma. Slight peppery orange. Flavour has the bitter hop taste but a very bland flavour. Again peppery. Expecting a hoppy bad boy with the name gale force IPA. More like a weak breeze IPA.
Bottle from brewdog brewery. Pours a clear light amber with a nice white frothy head. Aromas of cinnamon, cloves and pumpkin. Flavour is similar but not much pumpkin.
Bottle from deeside drinks. Pours a clear reddish brown with a caramel head. Aromas of peach, passion fruit and lychee. Flavour is again peachy with a nice grainy finish.
beer_name: The Kernel London Brick Collaboration Red Rye Ale

review_blob: Can from deeside drinks. Pours a clear Amber with little head. Aromas of coriander seed, light lemongrass. Flavour is rather bland. Slight peppery linger.

Can from deeside drinks emporium. Pours a clear yellow with a thin frothy head which fades slowly. Incredible aroma of pink grapefruit with a mild peppery tinge. Flavour is the same with a pine finish. Could drink this daily! Absolutely sublime.

Bottle from brewdog brewery. Labelled as Santa paws. Pours a dark ruby red with little head. Not much aroma. Some chocolate, flavour is dried fruits 
With again some chocolate. Not a usual brewdog beer.

Bottle from brewdog brewery. Pours a reddish Amber with a thin off white head that fades. Aromas of raisins, caramalised nuts and a slight floral tinge. Flavour is similar with a watery mouthfeel and not much body.
Bottle from the brother. Cheers Jamestulloch! Pours an amber gold with little head. Aromas of lime, slight pineapple and hay. Taste is similar with a bitter finish.
beer_name: Hooded Ram Little King Louis IPA

review_blob: Bottle from brewdog brewery. Pours a glazed jet black with a small, light brown head. Aromas of creamy coffee, burnt logs and milk chocolate. Flavour is similar and very moreish. Like an adults milkshake!

Bottle from brewdog brewery. Pours a dark hazy brown with a frothy off white head. Aromas of slightly burnt toast and coffee with a fruity chocolate orange. Taste is similar with a nice bitter linger. Thinner than expected but lovely all the same.

Can from Brewdog headquarters Ellon, pours a ruby red/brown with a small off white head. Aroma of pomegranate, berry jam with hints of pine and caramel. Flavour is earthy and dry with hints of orange peel and a pine hop finish. Excellent beer.

Bottle from the brother! Pours a hazed light yellow with a thin white frothy head that lasts. Very lively carbonation. Aromas of zesty citrus fruits, rhubarb, hay and pale malt. Flavour is zest of lemon, rhubarb and sour tangerines, lovely bitter saison. Would be an amazing summer beer.

Bottle shared with the bro. Pours a dark black with a dark brown head which fades. Aromas of coffee beans, raisins, roasted malts plums and sweet caramel. Flavour is mild bitter dark chocolate, caramel and coffee. Slight bitterness but unbelievably smooth with very little alcohol burn! Incredible beer.

Bottle from flavourly.com. Pours a clear dark amber with a small white head. Aromas of smokey bacon, sweet pine, honeyblossom and slight orange. Flavour is overpowering smoke which hides the ginger and a bit too sweet.
beer_name: Tempest / BrewDog Edinburgh Honey, Jamaican Me Ginger

review_blob: Bottle from deeside drinks. Pours a slightly hazed reddish brown with a yellow creamy head. Aroma of massive sandalwood, leather, slight creamy woody pot pure and a tinge of citrus. Taste is again sandalwood with pepper and a pine and citrus burst at the end. Lovely linger! Very unusual but an incredible ale!

Bottle from flavourly.com pours a lively light gold with a small white head that lasts. Aromas of lemon, fresh cut grass, passion fruit and pineapple. Taste is crisp citrus flavours with a pine finish.
